pulfalight.title: Integrate "Request" buttons for multiple levels of access

comments.body: This information is already available in the `accessRestrict` element: https://www.loc.gov/ead/tglib/elements/accessrestrict.html. The `@type` value here is the most valuable.
We may need to support cases where requests are pending curatorial approval.
This is going to be given a lower priority given the shift in Mudd Library staff availability for the current sprint.

pulfalight.title: Determine whether or not ReCAP items can be requested using Aeon

comments.body: This shouldn't be any different from items outside of ReCAP, as these items are definitely going to have a barcode. They can only currently be requested through Voyager *if* they don't have a barcode in the `<dsc2>`.

pulfalight.title: Support single sign-on authentication (SSO) using the CAS for institutional Princeton users (those with NetIDs)

comments.body: Both figgy and DPUL have needed to be changed later to accommodate people with guest accounts on CAS (i.e. non-princeton email addresses). It would probably be a good idea to ensure that's not an issue from the outset, here.

pulfalight.title: Provide access to institutional Princeton users (NetID-based authentication) to restricted digitized content

comments.body:
Certain groups have certain rights to material, this would be:

* Certain departments
* Certain classes

SecureSend, which is currently in place for material which is not digitized, would not address cases where classes need to access online material. The Toni Morrison collection may not be completely open, but must still remain available. These cases might be broken into separate issues, as these classroom cases are not high priorities.

pulfalight.title: Migrate the Solr Collection to the SolrCloud for pulfalight-staging
Shopping Cart feature set for supporting the selection of multiple containers for Aeon requests

comments.body:
Vue integration had no objections, but this feature set could be significantly large.

Perhaps linked to this might be a separate issue for exploring the Aeon API? Ideally, in the future, users should be able to submit requests with cookies would permit users to submit requests to Aeon between collections (without forcing reauthentication).
The best approach to this would be to create wireframes and mockups in order to initiate this process.
We also want to ensure that this is tracked closely to the MVP release, as we want integration to be addressed before the MVP is deployed.
